{
  "texts": [
    "Gu et al.(2016) introduced a coverage mechanism to addresses out-of-vocabulary (OOV) issues by copying words directly from the original text with a certain probability.",
    "Cohan et al. (2018) proposed a hierarchical decoder structure that treats the documents as a collection of paragraphs, achieving strong performance on summarization tasks involving lengthy articles.",
    "With the advent of pre-trained language models, researchers have started shifting from traditional deep learning approaches to leveraging pre-training models in pursuit of better summarization performance.",
    "Liu and Lapata(2019) proposed BERTSUM, which applied the pre-training BERT (Devlin et al., 2019) model to abstractive summarization.",
    "Aksenov et al. (2020) optimized BERT's encoding process using a sliding window strategy, improving its effectiveness for longer documents."
  ]
}